 POST: 🤝Our researchers have developed new technology which helps neurodiverse groups of children play and connect with one another. 

The wearable bracelet includes coloured buttons to activate a light colour signifying the play mode or activity of the children, and is selected by the wearer to show playing together🟩, playing alone 🟦 or wanting to play with others 🟨.

Co-designed with the children themselves, this playful and powerful tool supports inclusive communication without words—encouraging empathy, autonomy, and mutual understanding. 🙌

